Alot of servers are down right now, but no one has really commented on it. anyone else find it odd? The servers that where down last night where drunkduck, Keenspace, pair and kissthis. They may not be the biggest servers but they are the ones that websites I go to are on. *_* it made me cranky.

Heres another virius program for you, cookiecanning, it goes through the server, (you have to have it's 'intermate details' to do this)and it eats whatever shouldn't be there, it's basicly an anti-cookiemonster virus.
Ta-da and done. w00t

Yeah. This is an update covering about two weeks and I'll do another of friday.
Project is going gooood ish.
Here's a link to a writing newsgroup, it is not a writers newsgroup. Subtle but important difference.
atl.writing  http://groups.google.com.au/group/alt.writing/browse_thread/thread/2b05f66b111b08d5/ad0b94b7298da2ce?lnk=st&q=Writers+newsgroups&rnum=1&hl=en#ad0b94b7298da2ce

I found this interesting shareware called DarkLoad or something like that, use it if your internet is really slow but if it's not then don't as it will keep crashing.
I've done more inverstergating in the last few weeks of internet services in my area, we where supposted to have broadband capability by xmas. Now it's xmas next year. *sigh* ;_; very sad.
I found this viris ware called Cookiemonster, it's pretty cool. It goes into a server and backs up chosen files on them and thats it, you don't lose your stuff. But don't use it as it's illeagel. ~_~
and thats it, catch u friday.

Hi and low to everyone! I have finally decided what my website will be about (me= ^_^) My brother makes comics, funny ones. But he hasn't gotten a website for them yet. He calls the comics a work of Kanad inc, I told him that he should have some sub companies. Cerberus productions has joined with a little work by stush freelancing co. That means that me and my bros freind can all put stuff on the site. I'm going to make the site, It's going to be the collective works of both of us, with some cool stuff from stush. Thats some of the stuff he does (just so you know, thats me eating the sandwich)

Remember everyone PEBKAC That term has helped many in tech support over the years.
(Real questions)
Why does it delete my work when I turn the computer off? You need to save it?
Why isn't the music thingy making music?
How come Sims isn't working? What do you mean we don't have Sims?
I think I deleted the internet.
I defiantly deleted the internet.
I deleted the computer.
The computers making whining noises and is starting to smoke, is that bad?

To all this I say PEBKAC. It doesn't solve anything, but it lets others who do the same thing know what the trouble was. (Sorry, my sister claimed to have broken 'everything, it stopped working', she had accidentlly turned the screen off)

I have just finished tutorial 2, can someone say easy?

Here is some stuff that I have to write for the assignment.

a) My project is not really going anywhere, I was trying to decide between a review site for TV shows and one about teddy bears. Now I don't want to do either. Maybe I should just do one advertising my work?
b) I hope no one has done this one yet, http://www.textengineer.com/ it's a website that shows how to get coaching and stuff for you writing. You have to pay and I think it's in America.
c) I saw some interesting website layouts, www.aliendice.com (It's a comic website but the layout is reasonably easy to navigate) 
d) We got this program called add-aware, it gets rid of cookies that get attched to you. You also get to choose if they should be deleted.
e) Iprimis, my ISP. They have given us a deal, we use them for our internet line and our phone line and the internet is cheap. Phone line is crap. They constantly drop out (as in both phone lines), so its not exaclly reliable. In fact it isn't good at all, we want broadband but it isn't in our area yet.
f) Does that mean just pay attention to them? Or do we have to write about them too? I don't like the VET viris manager (it dislikes me too).
g) Do that in a minuet
h) umm, how about no?

Look it I have now answered all the questions a bit. Cool right?

Ja-ne, (Later)
